6. TROUBLESHOOTING COMMON ISSUES

FileNotFoundError: Model not found
Cause: The script cannot find semi_markov_model_aggregated.json.
Solution: Ensure the JSON file is in the same directory as the script, or provide the full path using the --model argument.

Alert logs show continuous "!!! ALERTA !!!"
Context: If the ICP is > 20 mmHg.
Explanation: This is correct behavior. It indicates an ongoing hypertensive crisis requiring immediate intervention. The monitor is designed not to silence itself during a crisis.

The monitor does not beep at 16 mmHg (High)
Context: The log shows [Vigilando...] instead of ALERTA.
Explanation: This is correct behavior (The Stability Filter). The AI has calculated that although the pressure is elevated, the trend is flat (stable) or decreasing, so there is no immediate risk of further deterioration. This prevents alarm fatigue.

Traceback: ZeroDivisionError
Cause: Older version of the code calculating trends on empty data arrays.
Solution: Ensure you are using the latest version of icp_online_monitor.py which includes the protection against division by zero in the _calculate_trend function.
